OL,3,CScientific breakthrough in dementia
OL,4,Cdiagnosis after 10 years research
OL,6,FAndy and Susan Thompson, who live near
OL,7,FWinchester, endured two years of
OL,8,Funcertainty before Andy was finally
OL,9,Fdiagnosed with Alzheimer's after
OL,10,Fhaving a lumbar puncture test.
OL,12,FSusan said: "It wasn't very quick at
OL,13,Fall. After a lot of backwards and
OL,14,Fforwards, they decided to send him for
OL,15,Fa lumbar puncture, and it was almost a
OL,16,Fyear before we got the results."
OL,18,FAndy added that the new test, means he
OL,19,Fcould have received his diagnosis
OL,20,Fafter just a simple blood test, which
OL,21,Fwould have been much easier for him.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
