OL,3,CScientific breakthrough in dementia
OL,4,Cdiagnosis after 10 years research
OL,6,FHe said: " (Getting a lumbar puncture
OL,7,Ftest) is a serious thing to do. It
OL,8,Finvolves having a specimen of material
OL,9,Ftaken from your body, very near to the
OL,10,Fspine. It could go horribly wrong.
OL,11,FIt's a bit of a risk."
OL,13,FConsultant Neurologist Professor Chris
OL,14,FKipps from University Hospital
OL,15,FSouthampton said: "If patients like
OL,16,FAndy are diagnosed early, then they
OL,17,Fcould potentially receive treatments
OL,18,Fto slow down the disease and have more
OL,19,Ftime to prepare for the future."
